Package com.gh.bmd.jrt.channel

Classes and interfaces related to routine channels.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Channel
    Interface defining a basic communication channel with the routine.
    InputChannel<INPUT>
    Interface defining an input channel.
    OutputChannel<OUTPUT>
    Interface defining an output channel, that is the channel used to read the routine invocation output data.
    OutputConsumer<OUTPUT>
    Interface defining an output consumer that can be bound to an output channel.
    The same instance can be safely bound to different output channels.
    ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Interface defining a parameter input channel, that is the channel used to pass input data to the routine invocation.
    ResultChannel<OUTPUT>
    Interface defining a result channel, that is the channel used by the routine invocation to publish the results into the output channel.
    StandaloneChannel<DATA>
    Interface defining a standalone channel.
    StandaloneChannel.StandaloneInput<INPUT>
    Interface defining a standalone channel input.
    StandaloneChannel.StandaloneOutput<OUTPUT>
    Interface defining a standalone channel output.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Channels
    Utility class for handling channels.
    Channels.Selectable<DATA>
    Data class storing information about the origin of the data.
    TemplateOutputConsumer<OUTPUT>
    Empty abstract implementation of an output consumer.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ReadDeadlockException
    Exception indicating that no result became available before the read timeout elapsed.
